3834  *   Post-Solve Checks ----------------------------------------------------------
3835   
3836  *   Check for disconnected nodes
          8.2 Dead Electrical Island
              If an Electrical Island > 2 has no positive load or if the total energy offered within the Electrical Island is zero then the Electrical Island is determined to be a dead
              Electrical Island and each ACNode in the Electrical Island is added to the set of DeadACNodes and each Pnode in the Electrical Island is added to the set of DeadPnodes.
          8.4 Disconnected Pnodes
              Each Pnode that has a scheduled load of zero and is in the set of DeadPnodes is added to the set of DisconnectedPnodes.
3844      busGeneration(bus(t,b)) = sum[ (o,n) $ { offerNode(t,o,n) and NodeBus(t,n,b) } , NodeBusAllocationFactor(t,n,b) * GENERATION.l(t,o) ] ;
3845      busLoad(bus(t,b))       = sum[ NodeBus(t,n,b), NodeBusAllocationFactor(t,n,b) * requiredLoad(t,n) ] ;
3846      busDisconnected(bus(t,b)) $ { ( [busElectricalIsland(bus) = 0] and [busLoad(bus) = 0] )
3847                                 or ( sum[ b1 $ { busElectricalIsland(t,b1) = busElectricalIsland(bus) } , busLoad(t,b1) ] = 0 )
3848                                 or ( sum[ b1 $ { busElectricalIsland(t,b1) = busElectricalIsland(bus) } , busGeneration(t,b1) ] = 0 ) } = 1 ;
3849   
3850  *   Energy Shortfall Check (7.2)
3851      if( (smax[t, dtParameter(t,'enrgShortfallTransfer')] = 1) and (LoopCount(ca,dt) < maxSolveLoops(ca,dt)),
3852   
3853  *       Check for dead nodes
3854          IsNodeDead(t,n) = 1 $ ( sum[b $ { NodeBus(t,n,b) and (busDisconnected(t,b)=0) }, NodeBusAllocationFactor(t,n,b) ] = 0 ) ;
3855          IsNodeDead(t,n) $ ( sum[b $ NodeBus(t,n,b), busElectricalIsland(t,b) ] = 0 ) = 1 ;
3856          NodeElectricalIsland(t,n) = smin[b $ NodeBusAllocationFactor(t,n,b), busElectricalIsland(t,b)] ;
3857          InputInitialLoad(t,n) $ { IsNodeDead(t,n) and (NodeElectricalIsland(t,n) > 0) } = 0;
3858   
3859  *       Check if a pnode has energy shortfall
3860          EnergyShortfallMW(t,n) $ Node(t,n) = ENERGYSCARCITYNODE.l(t,n) + sum[ b $ NodeBus(t,n,b), busNodeAllocationFactor(t,b,n) * DEFICITBUSGENERATION.l(t,b) ] ;
3861          EnergyShortfallMW(t,n) $ { IsNodeDead(t,n) and (NodeElectricalIsland(t,n) > 0) } = 0;
3862   
3863  *       a.Checkable Energy Shortfall:
3864  *       If a node has an EnergyShortfallMW greater than zero and the node has LoadIsOverride set to False and the Pnode has InstructedShedActivepn set to False, then EnergyShortfall is checked.
3865          EnergyShortFallCheck(t,n) = 1 $ { (EnergyShortfallMW(t,n) > 0) and (LoadIsOverride(t,n) = 0) and (instructedShedActive(t,n) = 0) } ;
3866   
3867  *       c. Eligible for Removal:
3868  *       An EnergyShortfall is eligible for removal if there is evidence that it is due to a modelling inconsistency (as described below),
3869  *       or if the RTD Required Load calculation used an estimated initial load rather than an actual initial load, or if the node is dead node.
3870          EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n) = 1 $ [EnergyShortFallCheck(t,n)  and { PotentialModellingInconsistency(t,n) or (useActualLoad(t) = 0) or (LoadIsBad(t,n) = 1) or (IsNodeDead(t,n) = 1) }] ;
3871   
3872  *       d. Shortfall Removal:
3873  *       If the shortfall at a node is eligible for removal then a Shortfall Adjustment quantity is subtracted from the requiredLoad in order to remove the shortfall.
3874  *       If the node is dead node then the Shortfall Adjustment is equal to EnergyShortfallMW otherwise it's equal to EnergyShortfall plus EnergyShortfallRemovalMargin.
3875  *       If the adjustment would make requiredLoad negative then requiredLoad is assigned a value of zero. The adjusted node has DidShortfallTransferpn set to True so that
3876  *       the RTD Required Load calculation does not recalculate its requiredLoad at this node
3877          ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n) $ EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n) = [ dtParameter(ca,dt,'shortfallRemovalMargin') $ (IsNodeDead(t,n) = 0) ] + EnergyShortfallMW(t,n) ;
3878   
3879          requiredLoad(t,n) $ EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n) = requiredLoad(t,n) - ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n) ;
3880          requiredLoad(t,n) $ { EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n) and (requiredLoad(t,n) < 0) } = 0 ;
3881          DidShortfallTransfer(t,n) $ EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n) = 1 ;
3882   
3883          loop( (t,n) $ EnergyShortfallMW(t,n),
3884              putclose rep 'Energy shortfall at node' n.tl,': ', EnergyShortfallMW(t,n)' MW. Eligible for shortfall removal: ' EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n):<1:0 /;
3885          ) ;
3886   
      e. Shortfall Transfer:
      If the previous step adjusts requiredLoad then the processing will search for a transfer target Pnode to receive the Shortfall Adjustment quantity (the search process is described below).
      If a transfer target node is found then the ShortfallAdjustmentMW is added to the requiredLoad of the transfer target node and the DidShortfallTransfer of the transfer target Pnode flag is set to True.
      k. Shortfall Transfer Target:
      In the Shortfall Transfer step, the search for a transfer target node proceeds as follows.
      The first choice candidate for price transfer source is the PnodeTransferPnode of the target Pnode. If the candidate is ineligible then the new candidate will be the PnodeTransferPnode of the candidate,
      if any, but only if this new candidate has not already been visited in this search. The process of locating and checking candidates will continue until an eligible transfer Pnode is located or until no
      more candidates are found. A candidate node isn't eligible as a target if it has a non-zero EnergyShortfall in the solution being checked or had one in the solution of a previous solve loop, or if the
      candidate node has LoadIsOverridepn set to True, or if the candidate node has InstructedShedActivepn set to True, or if the node with the shortfall is not in Electrical Island 0 and the ElectricalIsland
      of the candidate node is not the same as the ElectricalIslandpn of the node with the shortfall, or if the candidate node is in the set of DEADPNODESpn.
3899          unsolvedDT(t) = yes $ sum[n $ EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n), ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n)] ;
3900   
3901          while( sum[n, ShortfallAdjustmentMW(ca,dt,n)],
3902   
3903  * If target node is dead --> move it up to one level
3904              nodeTonode(t,n,n2) $ sum[n1 $ { nodeTonode(t,n,n1) and nodeTonode(t,n1,n2) }, IsNodeDead(t,n1)] = yes ;
3905              nodeTonode(t,n,n1) $ IsNodeDead(t,n1) = no ;
3906   
3907  * This is the approach SPD is using (a deficit node is ineligible as target node )
3908              nodeTonode(t,n,n2) $ sum[n1 $ { nodeTonode(t,n,n1) and nodeTonode(t,n1,n2) }, ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n1)] = yes;
3909              nodeTonode(t,n,n1) $ sum[n2 $ { nodeTonode(t,n,n2) and nodeTonode(t,n1,n2) }, ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n1)] = no;
3910   
3911  *           Check if shortfall from node n is eligibly transfered to node n1
3912              ShortfallTransferFromTo(nodeTonode(t,n,n1))
3913                  $ { (ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n) > 0)
3914                  and (LoadIsOverride(t,n1) = 0) and (InstructedShedActive(t,n1) = 0)
3915                  and [ (NodeElectricalIsland(t,n) = NodeElectricalIsland(t,n1)) or (NodeElectricalIsland(t,n) = 0) ]
3916                    } = 1;
3917   
3918  * This is the approach Tuong propose (a target node is ineligible as target node twice consecutively  ))
3919  *            nodeTonode(t,n,n2) $ sum[n1 $ nodeTonode(t,n1,n2), ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1)] = yes;
3920  *            nodeTonode(t,n,n1) $ ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1) = no;
3921   
3922              loop( nodeTonode(t,n,n1) $ ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1),
3923                 putclose rep 'Short fall adjustment from 'n.tl' to ', n1.tl,': ', ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n)' MW' /;
3924              ) ;
3925   
3926  *           If a transfer target node is found then the ShortfallAdjustmentMW is added to the requiredLoad of the transfer target node
3927              requiredLoad(t,n1) $ (IsNodeDead(t,n1) = 0)= requiredLoad(t,n1) + sum[ n $ ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1), ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n)] ;
3928              PotentialModellingInconsistency(t,n1) $ {(IsNodeDead(t,n1)=0) and sum[ n $ ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1), ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n)] } = 1;
3929   
3930  *           If a transfer target node is dead then the ShortfallAdjustmentMW is added to the ShortfallAdjustmentMW of the transfer target node
3931              ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n1) $ (IsNodeDead(t,n1) = 1) = ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n1) + sum[ n $ ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1), ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n)] ;
3932   
3933  *           and the DidShortfallTransfer of the transfer target node is set to 1
3934              DidShortfallTransfer(t,n1) $ sum[n, ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1)] = 1 ;
3935   
3936  *           Set ShortfallAdjustmentMW at node n to zero if shortfall can be transfered to a target node
3937              ShortfallAdjustmentMW(t,n) $ sum[ n1, ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1)] = 0;
3938              ShortfallTransferFromTo(t,n,n1) = 0;
3939   
3940          ) ;
3941   
3942  *       f. Scaling Disabled: For an RTD schedule type, when an EnergyShortfallpn is checked but the shortfall is not eligible for removal then ShortfallDisabledScalingpn is set to True
3943  *       which will prevent the RTD Required Load calculation from scaling InitialLoad.
3944          ShortfallDisabledScaling(t,n) = 1 $ { (EnergyShortFallCheck(t,n)=1) and (EligibleShortfallRemoval(t,n)=0) };
3945      ) ;
3946  *   Energy Shortfall Check End
3947   
3948      unsolvedDT(t) $ {(studyMode(t) = 101 or studyMode(t) = 201) and (LoopCount(t)=1) and (dailymode = 0)} = yes ;
3949      if ((studyMode(ca,dt) = 101 or studyMode(ca,dt) = 201) and sum[unsolvedDT(t),1] and (dailymode = 0),
3950          putclose rep 'Recalculate RTD Island Loss for next solve'/;
3951          LoadCalcLosses(t,isl)= Sum[ (br,frB,toB) $ { ACbranch(t,br) and branchBusDefn(t,br,frB,toB) and busIsland(t,toB,isl) }, sum[ fd, ACBRANCHLOSSESDIRECTED.l(t,br,fd) ] + branchFixedLoss(t,br) ]
3952                               + Sum[ (br,frB,toB) $ { HVDClink(t,br) and branchBusDefn(t,br,frB,toB) and ( busIsland(t,toB,isl) or busIsland(t,frB,isl) ) }, 0.5 * branchFixedLoss(t,br) ]
3953                               + Sum[ (br,frB,toB) $ { HVDClink(t,br) and branchBusDefn(t,br,frB,toB) and busIsland(t,toB,isl) and (not (busIsland(t,frB,isl))) }, HVDCLINKLOSSES.l(t,br) ] ;
3954  *        LoopCount(t) = LoopCount(t) + 1 ;
3955          loop( (t,isl) $ {unsolvedDT(t) and ( SPDLoadCalcLosses(t,isl) > 0 ) and ( abs( SPDLoadCalcLosses(t,isl) - LoadCalcLosses(t,isl) ) > SPDlossTolerance )},
3956              putclose rep 'Recalulated losses for ' isl.tl ' are different between vSPD (' LoadCalcLosses(t,isl):<10:5 ') and SPD (' SPDLoadCalcLosses(t,isl):<10:5 ') --> Using SPD calculated losses instead.' ;
3957  *            putclose rep 'Using SPDLoadCalcLosses instead. /' ;
3958              LoadCalcLosses(t,isl) = SPDLoadCalcLosses(t,isl);
3959   
3960          );
3961      ) ;
3962      LoopCount(t) = LoopCount(t) + 1 ;
3963      unsolvedDT(t) $ (LoopCount(t) > maxSolveLoops(t)) = no ;
